The River Deli is a Brooklyn Heights establishment. I have been living in the neighbourhood for a while and head down to the RH whenever I can find an excuse. Brunch is about the best excuse I can generally come up with. A macchiato (or three) is another goodie.  What I love about the RD is that it is quality with a lovely attention to detail and yet is not pretentious in the least. You will find all manner of people and tastes at this gorgeous spot along one of the prettiest streets (Joralemon) in Brooklyn.  And a stroll in the park after the meal is a lovely added benefit.

This is one of my newly discovered favorite restaurants. The atmosphere is warm, intimate and nostalgic. The wine recommended to me was right on with what I was asking for. Then the food came out! The shrimp appetizer was impressed with the way the sauce mixed with the spices on the shrimp. it had so many layers of flavor. In fact so did the main dish I ordered. I had the ltagliatelle Al Ragu Di Agnello which is a ragu made with lamb. There was a touch of cinnamon that deepened the flavor. It was bold and delicious.  Great place, great vibe, great food and great service. I highly recommend this spot for a best friend date night, a romantic evening or a small close group of friends.
